Maintainer: Travis Gerke <tgerke@mail.harvard.edu>
Description: Constructs CONSORT (Consolidated Standards of Reporting
    Trials) diagrams and other participant flow charts, such as PRISMA
    (Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and Meta-Analyses)
    diagrams, as 'ggplot2' plots. Cohorts are defined with 'dplyr'-style
    expressions and counted automatically, so box labels stay consistent
    with the underlying data; boxes are declared on a grid of rows and
    columns, and the layout is computed on the graphics device at draw
    time. For the CONSORT statement, see Schulz, Altman, and Moher (2010)
    <doi:10.1136/bmj.c332>.
